% layout 'wrapper-left';
<style>
.play-teochew { font-size: 1.5em }
</style>

<h1>Tones</h1>

<p>
There are 8 tones in Teochew. In many resources, you will see a number after
each syllable, indicating which tone it is.
</p>
<div class="row"><div class="col-md-6 offset-md-3">
<table class="table table-sm">
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Tone</th>
      <th>Description</th>
      <th colspan="4">Example</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>1</td>
      <td>Middle</td>
      %= include 'elements/translation-row', word => 'shirt'
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>2</td>
      <td>Falling</td>
      %= include 'elements/translation-row', word => 'hand'
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>3</td>
      <td>Low Falling, Rising</td>
      %= include 'elements/translation-row', word => 'vegetables'
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>4</td>
      <td>Middle Short</td>
      %= include 'elements/translation-row', word => 'meat'
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>5</td>
      <td>High</td>
      %= include 'elements/translation-row', word => 'head'
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>6</td>
      <td>Rising</td>
      %= include 'elements/translation-row', word => 'old'
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>7</td>
      <td>Low</td>
      %= include 'elements/translation-row', word => 'big'
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>8</td>
      <td>High Short</td>
      %= include 'elements/translation-row', word => 'white', pengim => 'beh8'
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>
</div></div>

<p>
Many words undergo tone change when placed in front of another word. This is
called <b>sandhi</b>. The table below shows the same words as above, but placed
in front of another word to demonstrate how their tones change.
</p>
<div class="row"><div class="col-md-6 offset-md-3">
<table class="table table-sm">
  <thead>
    <th>Original Tone</th>
    <th>Changed Tone</th>
    <th colspan="4">Example</th>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>1</td><td>1</td>
      %= include 'elements/translation-row', word => 'clothes'
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>2</td><td>6</td>
      %= include 'elements/translation-row', word => 'finger'
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>3</td><td>2 (or 5)</td>
      %= include 'elements/translation-row', word => 'radish'
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>4</td><td>8</td>
      %= include 'elements/translation-row', word => 'dried, shredded pork'
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>5</td><td>7</td>
      %= include 'elements/translation-row', word => 'hair (on your head)'
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>6</td><td>7</td>
      %= include 'elements/translation-row', word => 'great grandmother'
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>7</td><td>7</td>
      <%= include 'elements/translation-row',
            word => "aunt (dad's oldest sister)" %>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>8</td><td>4</td>
      %= include 'elements/translation-row', word => 'napa cabbage'
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>
</div></div>

<p>In the translations on this site, if a word has undergone tone change, the
spoken tone will be displayed in parentheses. If a word originally has tone 3 and undergoes tone change, I will always display tone 2 for it, but my audio clips will vary between actually saying it with tone 2 or tone 5. I'm not consistent ðŸ˜…
</p>
